{% comment %}
  Appends the current brand handle as an extra class on <body> (see layout/theme.liquid).
  layout/theme.liquid captures this once in <head> for the body class and for conditional @font-face: Bubbly (mr-bubble), Larken (village-naturals-therapy).

  HOW IT WORKS
  1) When sections['header'] is available, we render snippets/resolve-brand-handle.liquid
     with the header’s brand blocks — same rules as sections/header.liquid (full logic).
  2) When it isn’t (common in theme.liquid while <body> is rendering), we use the FALLBACK
     below so the body class still matches real brand context as closely as possible.

  KEEP IN SYNC WITH resolve-brand-handle.liquid
  The fallback only approximates parts of resolve-brand-handle that don’t need brand blocks:
    • URL / path / template.suffix heuristics — mirror the mr-bubble / therapy / soft-dri
      style checks there (add new brands or path hints here when you add them to the URL
      loop in resolve-brand-handle).
    • Product: product.vendor | handleize — same idea as the product {% for %} in resolve-brand-handle.
    • Blog: village-naturals-therapy + fun — same as the blog {% if %} in resolve-brand-handle.

  The fallback does NOT replicate: default brand, “The Village Co.” preference, mega menu
  active link, or per-block brand_page_link matching. If those change behavior in the header,
  body may still differ until sections['header'] is available in layout (rare) or we refactor.

  When you change brand selection rules in resolve-brand-handle.liquid, update this fallback
  for any new URL keywords, vendors, or blog handles you rely on for body.* CSS.
{% endcomment %}
{%- assign brand_body_handle = '' -%}
{%- if sections['header'] != blank -%}
  {%- assign header_brand_blocks = sections['header'].blocks | where: 'type', 'brand' -%}
  {%- if header_brand_blocks.size > 0 -%}
    {%- capture brand_handle_for_body -%}
      {%- render 'resolve-brand-handle', brand_blocks: header_brand_blocks -%}
    {%- endcapture -%}
    {%- assign brand_body_handle = brand_handle_for_body | strip -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- if brand_body_handle == blank -%}
  {%- liquid
    assign current_url = request.path
    assign url_segments = current_url | split: '/'
    assign last_segment = url_segments | last
    if template.suffix contains 'mr-bubble' or current_url contains 'mr-bubble' or last_segment contains 'mr-bubble'
      assign brand_body_handle = 'mr-bubble'
    elsif template.suffix contains 'therapy' or current_url contains 'therapy' or last_segment contains 'therapy'
      assign brand_body_handle = 'village-naturals-therapy'
    elsif template.suffix contains 'soft-dri' or current_url contains 'soft-dri' or last_segment contains 'soft-dri'
      assign brand_body_handle = 'soft-dri'
    endif
    if product and product.vendor != blank
      assign brand_body_handle = product.vendor | handleize
    endif
    if blog
      if blog.handle == 'village-naturals-therapy'
        assign brand_body_handle = 'village-naturals-therapy'
      elsif blog.handle == 'fun'
        assign brand_body_handle = 'mr-bubble'
      endif
    endif
  -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- if brand_body_handle != blank %} {{ brand_body_handle }}{% endif -%}
